description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit an enthusiastic Speech and Language Therapist to join the Learning Disability Inpatient Team, on Eastway Assessment and Treatment Unit in Chester. Eastway is a 9 bedded inpatient unit, offering assessment and treatment for adults with learning disabilities and additional complex challenging behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would be responsible for communication assessments, dysphagia assessments and providing appropriate advice and interventions. You would be required to work within a multi professional framework, supporting adults with learning disabilities, their families and carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an excellent communicator who will be able to contribute to Quality Improvement initiatives and projects that will have a significant impact on the health and wellbeing of people with a learning disability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a member of the RCSLT with 2 years post qualification experience including working with people with learning disabilities. The post is part time (18.75 hours) and permanent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:  Amanda Atkinson, Unit Manager, Email amanda.atkinson1@nhs.net Tel:  01244 397224&lt;/p&gt;
